defs.docs:
This crate is a Rust library for using the [Serde] serialization framework
 with data in [YAML] file format.

attributes.value: ! This crate is a Rust library for using the [Serde] serialization framework
! This library does not reimplement a YAML parser; it uses [yaml-rust] which
! is a pure Rust YAML 1.2 implementation.
!     // Serialize it to a YAML string.
!     // Deserialize it back to a Rust type.
! It can also be used with Serde's serialization code generator `serde_derive` to
! handle structs and enums defined in your own program.

allow(clippy :: should_implement_trait, clippy :: cast_lossless, clippy ::
        module_name_repetitions, clippy :: single_match_else, clippy ::
        use_self, clippy :: cast_possible_wrap, clippy :: cast_precision_loss,
        clippy :: cast_sign_loss, clippy :: indexing_slicing, clippy ::
        missing_docs_in_private_items, clippy :: checked_conversions, clippy
        :: empty_enum, clippy :: result_unwrap_used, clippy ::
        missing_errors_doc, clippy :: must_use_candidate,)

defs.name: from_str
defs.docs: Deserialize an instance of type `T` from a string of YAML text.

attributes.value: / Deserialize an instance of type `T` from a string of YAML text.
/ This conversion can fail if the structure of the Value does not match the
/ structure expected by `T`, for example if `T` is a struct type but the Value
/ contains something other than a YAML map. It can also fail if the structure
/ is correct but `T`'s implementation of `Deserialize` decides that something
/ is wrong with the data, for example required struct fields are missing from
/ the YAML map or some number is too big to fit in the expected primitive
/ YAML currently does not support zero-copy deserialization.
